title: ANZ lifts property investor interest rate
text:
Thu, Jul 23, 2015, 3:31 PM AEST - Australia Markets close in 29 mins. ANZ lifts property investor interest rate AAP – 31 minutes ago Print 
ANZ has lifted interest rates for property investors to comply with the banking regulator's efforts to slow investor lending growth. 
The bank has lifted its variable residential investment property loan rate by 0.27 per cent to 5.65 per cent in response to the Australian Prudential Regulatory Authority's efforts to slow the annual growth in investor loans to 10 per cent. 
There will be no change to variable rates for owner-occupied home loans or business lending. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Macquarie lifts full year guidance AAP
